  "risk_regime": {
    "stance": "risk_on",
    "conviction": 72,
    "rationale": "Eight of ten members are risk_on (Ali 70, Chris 85, Daren 70, Eddy 70, Guy 80, Jason 85, Miles 68, Kominers 72); the two abstentions (Thaler, Roughgarden) are cryptography/mechanism-design researchers who explicitly hold no market view rather than a cautious one, so they don't pull the consensus toward neutral. The bullishness is highly consistent in DIRECTION but uniformly qualified: it is long-horizon BUILDER optimism about foundational technology (zk/zkvm, L2s, restaking, AI x crypto, adoption metrics at all-time highs), NOT a tactical price or market-timing call. It is explicitly conditioned on (1) progress toward US regulatory clarity and (2) a sharp rejection of speculative 'casino' risk \u2014 the same desk that is risk-on for infrastructure is strongly risk-OFF on memecoins and 100x-leverage speculation. Consensus conviction is held to 72 (below the loudest individuals) because the posture is caveated and because the two most rigorous voices decline to express any market stance at all.",
    "provenance": "grounded"
  },
  "notes": "Consensus formed by weighting each item by conviction \u00d7 coverage; lone low-conviction views were faded and well-covered/high-conviction views allowed to dominate. SPLIT items (high stance_dispersion) were deliberately NOT placed in excited/concerned and are reported neutral here: (1) on-chain-adoption \u2014 coverage 2, stance_dispersion 1.0, mean sign 0: Daren is simultaneously bullish on rising adoption metrics AND bearish on the passive-ownership-vs-active-usage gap, so the desk has NO net stance. (2) pos-security \u2014 coverage 3, stance_dispersion 0.94, mean sign -0.33: almost entirely Roughgarden's nuanced research (the Merge increased economic security, but slashing/accountability face formal impossibility limits) plus Daren's mild staking positivity; this is analytical, not a directional market view, so treated as neutral/no-consensus. (3) permissionless-consensus-hardness \u2014 coverage 2, dispersion 1.0, sign 0: Roughgarden's possibility AND impossibility results net out. (4) BTC \u2014 coverage 2, stance_dispersion 1.0, mean sign 0: Guy's ideological endorsement (55) vs. Roughgarden's analytical structural-limitations framing (40); no consensus, held neutral. Important desk-wide caveat: this is overwhelmingly a builder/VC/researcher desk, NOT a trading desk \u2014 nearly all signal is STRUCTURAL conviction about technology and teams, with essentially no tactical price or macro-liquidity views. Token entries (ETH, SOL, EIGEN, NEAR, etc.) are therefore largely regulatory/adoption/infrastructure framings, not buy/sell calls, and are sparse by construction. The single most unifying axis across all ten members is a moral/strategic split: deeply bullish on mechanism-aligned, security-extending infrastructure and openly hostile to speculation-for-its-own-sake. No item was invented beyond the members' own named items; original item names retained throughout."
}